StatusReason.Description: The pipeline is ready to ingest data.

Pipeline.PipelineConfigurationBody:
version: "2"
log-pipeline:
  source:
    s3:
      codec:
        newline: # Other options "json", "csv", "parquet"
      # Provide compression property, can be "none", "gzip", or "automatic"
      compression: "none"
      aws:
        region: "us-east-1"
        sts_role_arn: "arn:aws:iam::644160558196:role/CloudCustodianRole"
      acknowledgments: true
      scan:
        # Define scan start and end times at scan level. Applicable for all buckets.
        # start_time: 2023-01-01T18:00:00
        # end_time: 2023-08-31T18:00:00
        # Alternatively scan can be defined as range as well. PT4H would scan all files created in the last 4 Hours.
        # Examples: "PT4H" or "PT30M" or "PT100S" or "P3D" or "P1W"
        # range: "PT4H"
        buckets:
          - bucket:
              # You can define scan start and end times at bucket level in addition to scan level.
              # Bucket level scan time always overwrites Scan level.
              # start_time: 2023-01-01T18:00:00
              # end_time: 2023-08-31T18:00:00
              # Scan start and end time can be defined as range as well. PT4H would scan all files created in the last 4 Hours.
              # range: "PT4H"
              name: "c7n-test-s3-bucket-copy"
      # delete_s3_objects_on_read: true # Default is false. This should be set to true only when acknowledgments are set to true
  processor:
    - date:
        destination: "@timestamp"
        from_time_received: true
    - delete_entries:
        with_keys: [ "s3" ]
  sink:
    - opensearch:
        # Provide an AWS OpenSearch Service domain endpoint
        hosts: [ "https://search-c7ntest-1a2a3a4a5a6a7a8a9a0a9a8a7a.us-east-1.es.amazonaws.com" ]
        aws:
          # Provide a Role ARN with access to the domain. This role should have a trust relationship with osis-pipelines.amazonaws.com
          sts_role_arn: "arn:aws:iam::644160558196:role/CloudCustodianRole"
          # Provide the region of the domain.
          region: "us-east-1"
          # Enable the 'serverless' flag if the sink is an Amazon OpenSearch Serverless collection
          serverless: false
          # serverless_options:
            # Specify a name here to create or update network policy for the serverless collection
            # network_policy_name: "network-policy-name"
        index: "uncompressed_logs"
        # Enable the 'distribution_version' setting if the AWS OpenSearch Service domain is of version Elasticsearch 6.x
        # distribution_version: "es6"
        # Enable and switch the 'enable_request_compression' flag if the default compression setting is changed in the domain. See https://docs.aws.amazon.com/opensearch-service/latest/developerguide/gzip.html
        # enable_request_compression: true/false
        # Optional: Enable the S3 DLQ to capture any failed requests in an S3 bucket. Delete this entire block if you don't want a DLQ.
